    purpose: "This policy keeps food from harming the people least able to survive its hazards. Frail and older people die from food poisoning that healthy adults shrug off, so the kitchen runs on the HACCP disciplines: hazards identified, controls at the points that matter, checks that prove the controls worked, and records that show it — every day, not inspection week.",
    scope: "Covers all food handling from delivery to plate in all settings where the service prepares or serves food: the documented food safety management system, temperature controls, personal hygiene and fitness rules, structural and equipment standards, and the adapted disciplines for small and domestic kitchens including supported living. The kitchen cleaning schedule detail sits with the Cleaning policy (saf-039) and this policy's appendix; allergens have their own policy (ch-003).",
